{"title_page": "Kenneth Berns", "text_new": "'''Kenneth I. Berns''' is an American virologist who is currently a Distinguished Professor Emeritus at the department of Molecular Genetics and Microbiology at the [[University of Florida College of Medicine]].<ref>http://mgm.ufl.edu/faculty/faculty-home-pages/kenneth-berns/</ref> He is primarily known for his work on [[adeno-associated viruses]] (AAV), and his group was one of the first which showed the specificty of the integration of the AAV genomes into the cellular genome.<ref name=\"pmid2156265\">{{cite journal| author=Kotin RM, Siniscalco M, Samulski RJ, Zhu XD, Hunter L, Laughlin CA | display-authors=etal| title=Site-specific integration by adeno-associated virus. | journal=Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A | year= 1990 | volume= 87 | issue= 6 | pages= 2211-5 | pmid=2156265 | doi=10.1073/pnas.87.6.2211 | pmc=53656 | url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/elink.fcgi?dbfrom=pubmed&tool=sumsearch.org/cite&retmode=ref&cmd=prlinks&id=2156265  }} </ref> He has been a member of the [[National Academy of Sciences]] since 1995.<ref>http://www.nasonline.org/member-directory/members/13166.html</ref>\n\n==References==\n", "text_old": "'''Kenneth I. Berns''' is an American virologist who is currently a Distinguished Professor Emeritus at the department of Molecular Genetics and Microbiology at the [[University of Florida College of Medicine]].<ref>http://mgm.ufl.edu/faculty/faculty-home-pages/kenneth-berns/</ref> He is primarily known for his work on [[adeno-associated virus]] (AAV), and his group was one of the first which showed the specificty of the integration of the AAV genome into the cellular genome.<ref name=\"pmid2156265\">{{cite journal| author=Kotin RM, Siniscalco M, Samulski RJ, Zhu XD, Hunter L, Laughlin CA | display-authors=etal| title=Site-specific integration by adeno-associated virus. | journal=Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A | year= 1990 | volume= 87 | issue= 6 | pages= 2211-5 | pmid=2156265 | doi=10.1073/pnas.87.6.2211 | pmc=53656 | url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/elink.fcgi?dbfrom=pubmed&tool=sumsearch.org/cite&retmode=ref&cmd=prlinks&id=2156265  }} </ref> He has been a member of the [[National Academy of Sciences]] since 1995.<ref>http://www.nasonline.org/member-directory/members/13166.html</ref>\n\n==References==\n", "name_user": "Amir.azhieh", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kenneth_Berns"}
{"title_page": "I'm Dangerous Tonight", "text_new": "{{Infobox television\n| italic_title         = \n| show_name            = I'm Dangerous Tonight\n| image                = Im-dangerous-tonight.jpg\n| image_upright        = \n| image_size           = \n| image_alt            = \n| caption              = Promotional poster\n| show_name_2          = \n| native_name          = <!-- {{Infobox name module|language|title}} or {{Infobox name module|title}} -->\n| genre                = [[Horror film|Horror]]{{sfn|Binion}}\n| creator              = \n| based_on             = <!-- {{Based on|work|author}} -->\n| developer            = \n| writer               = \n| screenplay           = {{plainlist|* [[Bruce Lansbury]]\n* Philip John Taylor{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}}}\n| story                = \n| director             = [[Tobe Hooper]]{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}\n| composer             = [[Nicholas Pike]]{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}\n| starring             = {{plainlist|*[[Madchen Amick]]\n* [[Corey Parker]]\n* Daisy Hall\n* [[R. Lee Ermey]]\n* [[Natalie Schafer]]}}\n| country              = United States{{sfn|Binion}}\n| language             = \n| executive_producer   = Boris Malden{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}\n| producer             = {{plainlist|* Bruce Lansbury\n* Philip John Taylor{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}}}\n| location             = \n| cinematography       =Levie Isaacks{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}\n| editor               = Carl Kress{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}\n| camera               = <!-- Either Single-camera or Multi-camera -->\n| runtime              = 92 minutes{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}\n| company              = \n| distributor          = \n| budget               = \n| network              = \n| picture_format       = \n| audio_format         = \n| released             = {{Start date|1990|8|8}}\n}}\n\n'''''I'm Dangerous Tonight''''' is a 1990 American [[television film|made-for-television]] [[supernatural horror film]] directed by [[Tobe Hooper]] and starring [[M\u00e4dchen Amick]], [[Corey Parker (actor)|Corey Parker]], [[R. Lee Ermey]] and [[Anthony Perkins]].{{sfn|Binion}} It made its debut on [[USA Network]] on August 8, 1990.\n\n==Plot==\nLoosely inspired by a novella by [[Cornell Woolrich]], the film revolves around a cursed [[Aztec]] ceremonial cloak that possesses anyone who wears it. Young college student Amy (Amick) decides to make a dress out of the cloth. Once she dons the dress, she falls under the spell and becomes a remorseless killer.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[M\u00e4dchen Amick]] - Amy\n*[[Corey Parker (actor)|Corey Parker]] - Eddie\n*Daisy Hall - Gloria\n*[[R. Lee Ermey]] - Lieutenant Ackman\n*[[Anthony Perkins]] - Professor Buchanan\n*[[Dee Wallace]] - Wanda Thatcher\n*[[William Berger (actor)|William Berger]] - Jonas Wilson\n*[[Natalie Schafer]] - Grandmother\n*[[Jason Brooks (actor)|Jason Brooks]] - Mason\n*[[Mary Frann]] - Martha\n*[[Stuart Fratkin]] - Victor\n\n==Production==\n''I'm Dangerous Tonight'' was produced for the [[USA Network]], a basic cable network in 1990.{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}} The film's story was based on a short story by [[Cornell Woolrich]].{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=151}}\n\n==Release==\n''I'm Dangerous Tonight'' was shown on the [[USA Network]] on August 10, 1990.\n{{sfn|Williams|1990}}\n\n==Reception==\nFrom contemporary reviews, Ken Tucker of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' gave the film a D ranking, declaring \"The only reason I watched this hokey-sounding TV movie was to see [[M\u00e4dchen Amick]], the much-abused Shelly, creepy Leo\u2019s wife, on ''[[Twin Peaks]]''.\"{{sfn|Tucker|1990}} Tucker noted that Amick \"goes from dedate college student to murderous temptress with ease\" while conlcuding that \"The rest of the movie is sanitized horror-movie piffle, with Anthony Perkins in a cameo role as \u2014 get this \u2014 a normal person.\"{{sfn|Tucker|1990}} Scott Williams writing for the [[Associated Press]] stated that the film \"is well-directed even if it isn't particlarly well-written.\" and that Hooper \"creates some scary images and is still prodding the material for thrills even when the script has run out of steam.\"{{sfn|Williams|1990}} Mike Duffy of the ''[[Detroit Free Press]]'' gave the film two stars stating it was a \"modest, melodramatic tale of the supernatural\" and that you should \"turn off the brian. \"''I'm Dangerous Tonight''\" won't work any other way.\"{{sfn|Duffy|1990}}\n\nIn a retrospective review, John Kenneth Muir in his book on Tobe Hooper found the film \"never quite as scary or as violent as fans know Tobe Hooper can make it.\" and that \"It isn't bad by any means, just fairly innocuous TV material.\"{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=151}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n===Sources===\n* {{cite web|url=https://www.allmovie.com/movie/im-dangerous-tonight-v24178|publisher=[[AllMovie]]|title=I'm Dangerous Tonight (1990)|accessdate=April 12, 2020|last=Binion|first=Cavett|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite newspaper|newspaper=[[Detroit Free Press]]|title=USA Dishes Melodrama 'Tonight'|last=Duffy|first=Mike||date=August 8, 1990|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|title=Eaten Alive at a Chainsaw Massacre: The Films of Tobe Hooper|last=Muir|first=John Kenneth|publisher=McFarland|year=2015|ref=harv|ISBN=1476613354}}\n* {{cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/1990/08/17/im-dangerous-tonight/|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|title=I'm Dangerous Tonight|date=August 17, 1990|last=Tucker|first=Ken|accessdate=April 12, 2020|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite newspaper|newspaper=[[Austin American-Statesman]]|date=August 8, 1990|last=Williams|first=Scott|page=B10|title='I'm Dangerous Tonight' elicits B-movie thrills|ref=harv}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|0099822}}\n* {{Amg movie|24178}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|im_dangerous_tonight|I'm Dangerous Tonight}} \n\n{{Tobe Hooper}}\n\n[[Category:1990 television films]]\n[[Category:1990 horror films]]\n[[Category:American supernatural horror films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:Horror television films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Tobe Hooper]]\n[[Category:USA Network original films]]\n[[Category:American television films]]\n\n{{US-tv-horror-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox television\n| italic_title         = \n| show_name            = I'm Dangerous Tonight\n| image                = Im-dangerous-tonight.jpg\n| image_upright        = \n| image_size           = \n| image_alt            = \n| caption              = Promotional poster\n| show_name_2          = \n| native_name          = <!-- {{Infobox name module|language|title}} or {{Infobox name module|title}} -->\n| genre                = [[Horror film|Horror]]{{sfn|Binion}}\n| creator              = \n| based_on             = <!-- {{Based on|work|author}} -->\n| developer            = \n| writer               = \n| screenplay           = {{plainlist|* [[Bruce Lansbury]]\n* Philip John Taylor{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}}}\n| story                = \n| director             = [[Tobe Hooper]]{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}\n| composer             = [[Nicholas Pike]]{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}\n| starring             = {{plainlist|*[[Madchen Amick]]\n* [[Corey Parker]]\n* Daisy Hall\n* [[R. Lee Ermey]]\n* [[Natalie Schafer]]}}\n| country              = United States{{sfn|Binion}}\n| language             = \n| executive_producer   = Boris Malden{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}\n| producer             = {{plainlist|* Bruce Lansbury\n* Philip John Taylor{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}}}\n| location             = \n| cinematography       =Levie Isaacks{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}\n| editor               = [[Carl Kress]]{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}\n| camera               = <!-- Either Single-camera or Multi-camera -->\n| runtime              = 92 minutes{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}}\n| company              = \n| distributor          = \n| budget               = \n| network              = \n| picture_format       = \n| audio_format         = \n| released             = {{Start date|1990|8|8}}\n}}\n\n'''''I'm Dangerous Tonight''''' is a 1990 American [[television film|made-for-television]] [[supernatural horror film]] directed by [[Tobe Hooper]] and starring [[M\u00e4dchen Amick]], [[Corey Parker (actor)|Corey Parker]], [[R. Lee Ermey]] and [[Anthony Perkins]].{{sfn|Binion}} It made its debut on [[USA Network]] on August 8, 1990.\n\n==Plot==\nLoosely inspired by a novella by [[Cornell Woolrich]], the film revolves around a cursed [[Aztec]] ceremonial cloak that possesses anyone who wears it. Young college student Amy (Amick) decides to make a dress out of the cloth. Once she dons the dress, she falls under the spell and becomes a remorseless killer.\n\n==Cast==\n*[[M\u00e4dchen Amick]] - Amy\n*[[Corey Parker (actor)|Corey Parker]] - Eddie\n*Daisy Hall - Gloria\n*[[R. Lee Ermey]] - Lieutenant Ackman\n*[[Anthony Perkins]] - Professor Buchanan\n*[[Dee Wallace]] - Wanda Thatcher\n*[[William Berger (actor)|William Berger]] - Jonas Wilson\n*[[Natalie Schafer]] - Grandmother\n*[[Jason Brooks (actor)|Jason Brooks]] - Mason\n*[[Mary Frann]] - Martha\n*[[Stuart Fratkin]] - Victor\n\n==Production==\n''I'm Dangerous Tonight'' was produced for the [[USA Network]], a basic cable network in 1990.{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=149}} The film's story was based on a short story by [[Cornell Woolrich]].{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=151}}\n\n==Release==\n''I'm Dangerous Tonight'' was shown on the [[USA Network]] on August 10, 1990.\n{{sfn|Williams|1990}}\n\n==Reception==\nFrom contemporary reviews, Ken Tucker of ''[[Entertainment Weekly]]'' gave the film a D ranking, declaring \"The only reason I watched this hokey-sounding TV movie was to see [[M\u00e4dchen Amick]], the much-abused Shelly, creepy Leo\u2019s wife, on ''[[Twin Peaks]]''.\"{{sfn|Tucker|1990}} Tucker noted that Amick \"goes from dedate college student to murderous temptress with ease\" while conlcuding that \"The rest of the movie is sanitized horror-movie piffle, with Anthony Perkins in a cameo role as \u2014 get this \u2014 a normal person.\"{{sfn|Tucker|1990}} Scott Williams writing for the [[Associated Press]] stated that the film \"is well-directed even if it isn't particlarly well-written.\" and that Hooper \"creates some scary images and is still prodding the material for thrills even when the script has run out of steam.\"{{sfn|Williams|1990}} Mike Duffy of the ''[[Detroit Free Press]]'' gave the film two stars stating it was a \"modest, melodramatic tale of the supernatural\" and that you should \"turn off the brian. \"''I'm Dangerous Tonight''\" won't work any other way.\"{{sfn|Duffy|1990}}\n\nIn a retrospective review, John Kenneth Muir in his book on Tobe Hooper found the film \"never quite as scary or as violent as fans know Tobe Hooper can make it.\" and that \"It isn't bad by any means, just fairly innocuous TV material.\"{{sfn|Muir|2015|p=151}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n===Sources===\n* {{cite web|url=https://www.allmovie.com/movie/im-dangerous-tonight-v24178|publisher=[[AllMovie]]|title=I'm Dangerous Tonight (1990)|accessdate=April 12, 2020|last=Binion|first=Cavett|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite newspaper|newspaper=[[Detroit Free Press]]|title=USA Dishes Melodrama 'Tonight'|last=Duffy|first=Mike||date=August 8, 1990|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book|title=Eaten Alive at a Chainsaw Massacre: The Films of Tobe Hooper|last=Muir|first=John Kenneth|publisher=McFarland|year=2015|ref=harv|ISBN=1476613354}}\n* {{cite web|url=https://ew.com/article/1990/08/17/im-dangerous-tonight/|work=[[Entertainment Weekly]]|title=I'm Dangerous Tonight|date=August 17, 1990|last=Tucker|first=Ken|accessdate=April 12, 2020|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite newspaper|newspaper=[[Austin American-Statesman]]|date=August 8, 1990|last=Williams|first=Scott|page=B10|title='I'm Dangerous Tonight' elicits B-movie thrills|ref=harv}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|0099822}}\n* {{Amg movie|24178}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|im_dangerous_tonight|I'm Dangerous Tonight}} \n\n{{Tobe Hooper}}\n\n[[Category:1990 television films]]\n[[Category:1990 horror films]]\n[[Category:American supernatural horror films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\